## COST COMPARISON BREAKDOWN (Critical for Content)

### SALON VALENTINE MANICURE
- **Basic gel manicure:** $45-60
- **Gel with simple Valentine art:** $55-75
- **Gel with rhinestones/3D art:** $70-100
- **Frequency:** Every 2 weeks = 2x in February
- **Monthly cost:** $90-150
- **Annual cost (1x/month):** $540-720

### COMPLETE KIT OPTION
- **Beginner gel kit:** $40-60
- **Includes:** UV lamp, gel polish (4-6 colors), base/top coat, tools
- **Cost per use:** $40-60 ÷ 20+ uses = $2-3 per manicure
- **Break-even point:** 1-2 uses (vs salon)
- **First year savings:** $480-660 (after kit cost)

### INDIVIDUAL SUPPLIES OPTION
- **UV/LED Lamp:** $25-35
- **Gel polish set (6 colors):** $20-30
- **Base & top coat:** $10-15
- **Nail files, buffers:** $8-12
- **Dotting tools, brushes:** $8-12
- **Heart stickers/rhinestones:** $10-15
- **Total:** $81-119
- **Cost per use:** $81-119 ÷ 20+ uses = $4-6 per manicure
- **Break-even point:** 2-3 uses (vs salon)
- **First year savings:** $421-639 (after supply costs)

### VERDICT FOR CONTENT
**Complete Kit Wins for Beginners:** Lower upfront cost ($40-60), everything included, breaks even fastest (1-2 uses). Recommended for first-time DIYers.

**Individual Supplies for Experienced:** More upfront ($81-119) but better quality/customization. Recommended for those who've tried kits and want to upgrade.

**Salon for Special Occasions:** Best for complex art, guaranteed results, zero learning curve. Worth it 1-2x/year for events.

